1. *Scena* je bila postavljena za novogodišnju predstavu. (The stage was set for the New Year's play.)
2. U pozorištu je bilo mnogo *scena* i rekvizita. (There were many scenes and props in the theater.)
3. Glumac je odigrao sjajnu *scenu*. (The actor played a brilliant scene.)
4. Na muzičkoj *sceni* u Srbiji ima mnogo talentovanih izvođača. (There are many talented performers in the music scene in Serbia.)
5. Nekoliko ljudi je bilo uhapšeno na *sceni* zločina. (Several people were arrested at the scene of the crime.)
6. Kada su se vrata otvorila, pred nama se ukazala prelepa *scena*. (When the doors opened, a beautiful scene appeared before us.)
7. *Scena* se promenila, a publika je počela da zviždi. (The scene changed and the audience started to boo.)
8. Glumci su vežbali *scenu* tokom celog dana. (The actors rehearsed the scene all day long.)
9. Na *sceni* se pojavila glavna glumica i svi su je pozdravili aplauzom. (The main actress appeared on stage and everyone greeted her with applause.)
10. Kada je snimanje *cene* završeno, svi su se razišli. (When the scene was finished filming, everyone dispersed.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "scena" can mean both "stage" and "scene" depending on the context.